Nigerian Afrobeat star Burna Boy won the Best Act in Africa award at the All Africa Music Awards (Afrima) on Sunday in Senegalâ€™s capital, Dakar. He also won the Best Album of Year award. Fellow Nigerian star Asake took home the Breakout Artist of the Year prize, while Ivorian singer, Didi B, won the Song of the Year award. Afrobeats stars Wizkid and Davido bagged the Best Act in West Africa award and the Best Male Act in African Inspirational Music award respectively. The Afrima awards are held every year to celebrate the best music from the continent.